<paragraph id="7D4236B75734B241FF2D6AB9FD676750" blockId="6.[151,1127,475,562]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">
Given the extreme similarity among species belonging to the 
<taxonomicName id="BAFD4D345734B241FCAD6AB9FC0F6490" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[821,967,475,498]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Oulema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanopus">
